A jet of flames burst from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set a specific part of the forest on fire, then flew in a circle above, observing it for a moment. Strangely, as it had slowed down, the odd noises of cries behind him had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't get suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's not so bad, isn't it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi; he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws into Thassalin's back, so much so that he had made the Thraki bleed, but evidently, he didn't care much. That said, Thassalin had realized that he had frightened his new friends and had found a clearing to land in.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SNIFFED A SMELL. I HAD TO CHECK."
"Did you have to drag us here with you?" Tenuk asked as he slid down from Thassalin's back along his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our big and strong fighter! How will he join us?"
"He'll find a way," Nissy replied. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive anything like Kayel's cute little car either. And if he started coming to work by car, it's only because YOU drive us there. He just has this bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly hilarious, and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him a bit too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINIATURE BIKE MEANT FOR CHILDREN OF THE TEMTHAN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WOULD HAVE WANTED TO BE TELPATHIC. THAT WAS A PRECIOUS THOUGHT! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel snickered, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's just it. But what did you pick up and why did you fly off so quickly?"
Thassalin grumbled, took off, and disappeared briefly before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a golden and white draconic creature, very rare. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I SENSE THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel did as well, their attention drawn by a break in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, this thing opened two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, without worrying about the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk barely managed to take cover, but Nyssi found herself dragged along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nissy and throwing her onto his back, using his tail, which was of extraordinary length and dexterity, before taking off. The two-winged black creature quickly gave chase.
Kayel exhaled and drew the rifle he had on his back, then opened a compartment where a belt of ammunition was located. He put it over his shoulder so he could access it easily, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to turn into something that can fly?" asked Kayel.
"You want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And so what? I have an ultra powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to be used. I just need to see it to shoot at it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to make some space. With a weak, slightly pained growl, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly became the normal light blue Thraki again, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb."
Having regained a more normal Thraki appearance, Tenuk now had his back covered in scale plates, but a pair of spikes had also grown on it, useful for Kayel to grip onto. Tenuk needed a bit of time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid it.
I suppose this is the other scary big monster that worried Lanex? Kayel frowned while trying to shoot at the second creature, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk did not react. He was too focused on his flight toward Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature chasing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the upper wings of the creature, which screamed in pain before disappearing again beneath the trees. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but it certainly wouldn't be able to catch up.
Further away, Nyssi was desperately clinging on, while Thassalin flew in circles, firing bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight, and the fireballs didn't seem to have the intended effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her weapon, a reliable rifle. Of course, it wasn't designed for this kind of situation, but a volley of shots would surely at least dissuade the black beast, right?
